    "updated_at": "2024-08-20T07:49:32Z",
    "body": "Hi, sorry for the long silence.\r\n\r\nThe thing is though that a) the docs don't say anything about `fg:none` specifically/specially, they only mention `none` on its own for styles, and b) `fg:<color>` is talking only about the color (in my case no color) as per the docs, so shouldn't affect anything else - in fact the docs then give an example with `bg:none` to prove the same point and functionality.  On that note, if there's support for clearing bg color then why not clearing fg color?\r\n\r\nI don't see how this is anything but a bug or at least (an undocumented) misfeature or a duplicate feature at best.  I'm open to seeing it your way but the docs are on my side :stuck_out_tongue: .  I also think it dubious that anyone would really be using `fg:none` when they mean `none`, and if they do it's a very easy migration.",
